    "body": "I have build a compiler that generates some pyx code. Can you tell me how to properly load (reload) a module using pyximport? Note that this code is run several times, and each module must remain usable. The code that doesnt work: \r\n```py\r\nimport pyximport\r\npyximport.install()\r\nimport imp\r\nwith open(\"construct_compile_target.pyx\",\"wt\") as f:\r\n    f.write(source)\r\nmodule = imp.load_source(\"construct_compile_target\", \"construct_compile_target.pyx\")\r\n```\r\nTest suite uses pytest:\r\n```py\r\nE     File \"construct_compile_target.pyx\", line 10\r\nE       cdef bytes read_bytes(io, count):\r\nE                ^\r\nE   SyntaxError: invalid syntax\r\n```",
